{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":135746,"duration_api_ms":220549,"num_turns":12,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a7ecb6c1-d07f-4d9c-a7a8-8ef2e1fecf1a","total_cost_usd":1.0482664499999998,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":73460,"cache_read_input_tokens":272545,"output_tokens":3335,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":73460,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":214,"outputTokens":13911,"cacheReadInputTokens":1665387,"cacheCreationInputTokens":106525,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.36946395,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":3335,"cacheReadInputTokens":272545,"cacheCreationInputTokens":73460,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.6788025,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 83 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","fr-9-f0ca9b46 VERIFIED: Shared render_completion_journal_details() in model.rs:347-379 is now the single rendering implementation. service.rs calls it via TaskRunEntry::completion_journal_details() at line 581. fs.rs CompletionJournalDetails::render() at line 2352 delegates directly to the same shared function. No duplicate implementations remain (confirmed by grep).","fr-9-1fa4f2f8 VERIFIED: CompletionJournalDetails::parse() in fs.rs:2281-2284 has an explanatory comment documenting that project_id/run_id/plan_hash are simple identifiers. render_completion_journal_details() in model.rs:354-365 has three debug_assert! statements enforcing that these fields never contain ', '.","fr-9-f4e1cccb VERIFIED: update_task_run fallback in fs.rs:2820-2864 now has explicit branches: [index] if entries[*index].run_id.is_none() accepts the single legacy runless row, [index] with a different run_id rejects (lines 2847-2854), and _ (multiple open matches including mixed legacy/named) rejects as ambiguous (lines 2856-2862). Regression test at service.rs:2900-2943 seeds [run_id=None, Running] + [run_id=run-2, Running], calls update with run_id=run-3, and asserts 'ambiguous task run update' error with no rows modified.","fr-9-6ff93073 VERIFIED: collapse_task_run_attempts() in model.rs:475-494 now groups entries by same_attempt via can_collapse_attempt_entries() (which allows collapsing duplicate terminals with matching outcomes) and merges each group via collapse_task_run_group(). Model test collapse_task_run_attempts_deduplicates_terminal_replays (model.rs:720-765) seeds 1 Running + 2 Succeeded rows for the same attempt and verifies collapse to 1 entry. Integration test find_runs_for_bead_deduplicates_replayed_terminal_rows (service.rs:1516-1589) seeds 3 NDJSON rows and verifies bead query returns 1 collapsed entry with merged metadata."],"findings_or_gaps":["All four final-review amendments (fr-9-f0ca9b46, fr-9-1fa4f2f8, fr-9-f4e1cccb, fr-9-6ff93073) have been addressed with code changes and regression tests in completion round 10.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs line 555 approximately) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","The active_bead_ids() function in model.rs still contains its own internal latest_task_runs_per_bead() call while reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage computes latest runs separately. External callers of active_bead_ids would redundantly recompute, but this is minor and outside the scope of the current amendments."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"50806815-dcb0-44ae-b791-28fee22a8235"}
